race.description: Mane Lodge Spelling & Transport Maiden Handicap
race.comment: FIERCE CRITIC (6) had been well educated and did a good job at Kembla Grange on debut after being last away. Draws inside today and the in-form Boudvillain is engaged. Strips fitter and won't have to improve much to take this out. The local COLORADO SUN (3) missed a whisker at Wagga first-up and then went back and has no luck at all over this distance, backed into red figures. Has good ability and the winkers go on for the first time. Heywood stays aboard and a much sharper effort is anticipated. MASTER OF WAR (2) is a stablemate to the top selection and showed enough at Newcastle on debut to consider over the longer sprint. LISTEN SWEETHEART (8) resumes and four back was tried in  Stakes grade on debut. Her numbers stack up and she has two trials under the saddle. Draws low and the blinkers come off. The late betting will be key.
